first_para: Alec Edward Shelbrooke (born 10 January 1976) is a British Conservative Party politician, who was elected at the 2010 general election as the Member of Parliament (MP) for Elmet and Rothwell, a new constituency created as a result of changes made by the Boundary Commission for England. The seat was Conservative target number 107.
